$interpreted: Chiyuki: Master...?
Master Orchid: Good, you're awake. How are you feeling?
Chiyuki: I'm okay, I guess. I feel like I've just awakened from a deep sleep.
Master Orchid: It's been about a day.
Chiyuki: A day!? What about Mayday? I don't remember what happened too clearly, it's like my consciousness left my body...
Master Orchid: Don't worry. I'll explain everything...
Chiyuki: Did I beat him...? How did he...
Master Orchid: You focussed the entirety of your mind upon the moment, and released all your inner strength in a miraculous single breath.
Chiyuki: I really... can't remember a thing...
Master Orchid: That's because you entered a selfless state. It's normal, the first time. You'll get used to it eventually.
Chiyuki: And what about the duel Mayday challenged me to?
Master Orchid: Oh, ignore that.
Chiyuki: But...
Master Orchid: Your studies are complete. It's time for you to leave the Peaks.
Chiyuki: Master... Why are you pressing me to leave, all of a sudden?
Master Orchid: Have you forgotten about the Alliance Beauty, Chiyuki?
Chiyuki: I... Of course not.
Master Orchid: There you go. You should get back to pursuing your dreams, instead of letting yourself get mixed up in things here.
Chiyuki: But I...
Master Orchid: I'm so proud to have had a student like you.
Chiyuki: Master...
Master Orchid: Try not to think too much about it. That's just the way of fate. Now, you should pack your bags and set off down the mountain, while it's still light out.
Chiyuki: (As soon as I've left here, I'll be back to following my dreams again...)
Chiyuki: (Have I really learned everything there is for me to know already...?)
Mayday: I knew it. That little weasel Orchid's forcing you out.
Chiyuki: What are you doing here!?
Mayday: Waiting for you, of course.
Chiyuki: For me?
Mayday: How would you like to join me, Miss?
Chiyuki: Forget it. You're just a scoundrel who plays tricks with perfume!
Mayday: I'm just doing whatever it takes to reach a higher realm of beauty. In that respect I'm no different from Master Orchid, you see.
Chiyuki: It's totally different! Stop twisting Master's ideas.
Mayday: And you, do you really think you understand him? Why do you think he's making you leave?
Chiyuki: Because he knows I have other paths to walk ahead of me.
Mayday: Wrong. He's afraid that you'll lose the duel.
Chiyuki: No way! Master said I've come so far already!
Mayday: You fluked out. Don't be so naive.
Chiyuki: That's still better than running off when the going gets tough.
Mayday: Haha~ You really don't understand the meaning of the duel.
Chiyuki: What?
Mayday: When two schools of thought clash, the two sides will send representatives to compete against each other. The winner becomes the Master, and the loser—must leave forever.
Mayday: That is the meaning of the duel.
Chiyuki: Doesn't that mean...
Mayday: Yep, if the Last Orchid's disciple were to lose, he too would be expelled.
Mayday: You see, he had no faith in you whatsoever.
Chiyuki: No... No, Master wouldn't do that.
Mayday: Don't be sad. I can still appreciate you.
Chiyuki: Appreciate me?
Mayday: Your charm, like the charm of the first snowfall. With a little of my guidance, you could surely rock the whole world with your blizzardlike elegance.
Chiyuki: Rock the world...
Mayday: Think about it. Alliance Beauty isn't the only thing you yearn for. Join me, and you could conquer everybody and everything~
Chiyuki: Conquer...
Chiyuki: Thank you, everyone. Thanks for your support.
Dazed Audience: Chiyuki... Chiyuki...
Chiyuki: No! I'm not like you!
Chiyuki: I've never wanted to conquer anybody. I... I just want my audience to appreciate beauty, to feel it.
Mayday: Pah! You think you'll ever reach the top by clinging to such childish ideals?
Chiyuki: I may not be bright, but I'll never stop pursuing my dreams! And before I do, I'll represent Master Orchid and beat you in that duel, too!
Mayday: Interesting. I'll unleash my most intoxicating, most ravishing butterflies and swallow up your damp squib of a snowfall!
